WARNING:EMAIL_SUBJECT: A patch subject line should describe the change not the tool that found it
#19: 
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] ide-disk: fix issues found by checkpatch.pl

Naming the tool that found the issue is not very useful in the
subject line.  A good subject line summarizes the change that
the patch brings.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/submitting-patches.html#describe-your-changes

WARNING:PREFER_PR_LEVEL: Prefer [subsystem eg: netdev]_info([subsystem]dev, ... then dev_info(dev, ... then pr_info(...  to printk(KERN_INFO ...
#265: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:825:
+	printk(KERN_INFO "%s: max request size: %dKiB\n", drive->name,

CHECK:PARENTHESIS_ALIGNMENT: Alignment should match open parenthesis
#266: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:826:
+	printk(KERN_INFO "%s: max request size: %dKiB\n", drive->name,
+			 drive->queue->max_sectors / 2);

WARNING:PREFER_PR_LEVEL: Prefer [subsystem eg: netdev]_info([subsystem]dev, ... then dev_info(dev, ... then pr_info(...  to printk(KERN_INFO ...
#281: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:842:
+			printk(KERN_INFO "%s: cannot use LBA48 DMA - PIO mode"

WARNING:SPLIT_STRING: quoted string split across lines
#282: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:843:
+			printk(KERN_INFO "%s: cannot use LBA48 DMA - PIO mode"
+					 " will be used for accessing sectors "

Quoted strings that appear as messages in userspace and can be
grepped, should not be split across multiple lines.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20120203052727.GA15035@leaf/

WARNING:SPLIT_STRING: quoted string split across lines
#283: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:844:
+					 " will be used for accessing sectors "
+					 "> %u\n", drive->name, 1 << 28);

CHECK:COMPARISON_TO_NULL: Comparison to NULL could be written "!idkp"
#303: FILE: drivers/ide/ide-disk.c:1011:
+	if (idkp == NULL)

Comparisons to NULL in the form (foo == NULL) or (foo != NULL)
are better written as (!foo) and (foo).

